Paper: hep-th/9411147

Date: 1994-11-20

Title: Quantum Dilogarithm as a 6j-Symbol

Authors: R. M. Kashaev

Comments: 12 pages, TeX; references added

Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A9 (1994) 3757-3768

The cyclic quantum dilogarithm is interpreted as a cyclic 6j-symbol of theWeyl algebra, considered as a Borel subalgebra $BU_q(sl(2))$. Using modified6j-symbols, an invariant of triangulated links in triangulated 3-manifolds isconstructed. Apparently, it is an ambient isotopy invariant of links.